# Sova (`brain-web`) UI — locked conventions

## Stack (do not replace)

- **Layout & chrome**: shadcn **Sidebar** via [`AppShell`](apps/brain-web/components/app-shell.tsx) only. Primary nav = **Opportunities** (`/`, `/opportunity/*`) and **Output** (`/output/*`). Do not add a second top-level nav pattern or duplicate headers outside this shell.
- **Output**: When route is under `/output`, show the **secondary channel nav** (Facebook, LinkedIn, Email, Blog/Newsletter) as today — desktop aside + mobile horizontal strip. Channel stubs live under [`components/output/`](apps/brain-web/components/output/); routes [`/output/[channel]`](apps/brain-web/app/(app)/output/[channel]/page.tsx).
- **Components**: Use primitives from [`@/components/ui/*`](apps/brain-web/components/ui/) (shadcn/Base UI). Add new UI via `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add …` from `apps/brain-web` so [`components.json`](apps/brain-web/components.json) (style **base-nova**, **lucide**, CSS variables) stays the source of truth.
- **Icons**: **lucide-react** only for app chrome and nav.
- **Styling**: **Tailwind v3** + semantic tokens (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `bg-sidebar`, `text-sidebar-foreground`, `primary`, etc.). Prefer these over raw hex in new code. **Dark**: root [`layout.tsx`](apps/brain-web/app/layout.tsx) keeps `className="dark"` on `<html>` — do not remove.
- **Global CSS**: [`globals.css`](apps/brain-web/app/globals.css) holds legacy helpers (`.card`, `.meta`, `.badge`, `.evidence`, `.actions`) for the opportunities feed/detail; keep using them there for visual consistency unless intentionally redesigning the whole feed.

## Root layout (do not strip)

- Wrap the app in [`TooltipProvider`](apps/brain-web/components/ui/tooltip.tsx) (see [`app/layout.tsx`](apps/brain-web/app/layout.tsx)).
- Route group [`app/(app)/`](apps/brain-web/app/(app)/) wraps **all** main UI pages in `AppShell`; API routes stay under `app/api/`.

## Sidebar rail

- Do **not** restore a **full-height** `SidebarRail` (`inset-y-0` spanning the column). The rail must stay a **short, centered** edge handle as in [`sidebar.tsx`](apps/brain-web/components/ui/sidebar.tsx).

## Anti-patterns

- ❌ Raw `<header>`/`<main>` page chrome duplicating Sova branding outside `AppShell`.
- ❌ MUI, Chakra, ad-hoc component libraries, or inline `style={{}}` for layout/spacing in new features.
- ❌ Replacing `@tailwind` + `tailwind.config.ts` theme tokens with one-off colors for the same role (background, border, sidebar).
- ❌ New “Output” channels without a matching stub under `components/output/` and entry in [`lib/output-channels.ts`](apps/brain-web/lib/output-channels.ts).

## File map (where things go)

| Area | Location |
|------|----------|
| shadcn primitives | `apps/brain-web/components/ui/` |
| Opportunities UI | `apps/brain-web/components/opportunities/` |
| Output channel stubs | `apps/brain-web/components/output/` |
| App shell (sidebars) | `apps/brain-web/components/app-shell.tsx` |

When unsure, match patterns in existing `OpportunitiesFeed`, `AppShell`, and `components/ui/*`.
